A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 31C of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 the "Completion Special Schools Act," so as to require certain local school systems to either
3 be a party to a collaborative operating agreement with a completion special school or provide
4 certain education programs and services to students in grades nine through 12; to require
5 local school systems to provide to completion special schools the contact information for
6 students who stop attending or withdraw from the local school system, subject to conditions
7 and exceptions; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
8 purposes.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
10 SECTION 1.
11 Article 31C of Chapter 2 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, the
12 "Completion Special Schools Act," is amended by adding a new Code section to read as
13 follows:
14 "20-2-2096.9.
15 (a) Each local school system with all or part of its territory within the attendance zone of
16 one or more operating completion special schools shall:
